WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:11.260
Most of you will remember that we are dealing at the moment with the words found in Paul's Epistle to the Romans in chapter 11, from verse 18 to the end of the 22nd verse.

00:11.941 --> 00:17.830
Verse 18 to 22 in the 11th chapter of Paul's Epistle to the Romans.

00:19.272 --> 00:25.582
Verse not against the branches, but if thou burst now, bearest not the root, but the root thee.

00:26.724 --> 00:27.986
Thou will say then,

00:28.322 --> 00:31.507
The branches were broken off that I might be grafted.

00:32.368 --> 00:38.657
Well, because of unbelief, they were broken off, and thou standest by faith.

00:39.598 --> 00:47.830
Be not high-minded but fear, for if God spared not the natural branches, take heed lest he also spare not thee.

00:49.412 --> 00:56.242
Behold, therefore, the goodness and severity of God, on them which fell in the severity.

00:57.122 --> 01:05.490
But toward the goodness, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise thou also shalt be cut off."

01:06.391 --> 01:17.462
Now, this is the most important statement, one of these great crucial statements that are to be found scattered about in the pages of World Erect.

01:17.622 --> 01:21.546
And this is an unusually important one for many, many reasons.

01:21.946 --> 01:25.970
We've spent some time in expounding it, I mean by that in

01:26.146 --> 01:30.291
showing the exact meaning of the words and what the statement is in general.

01:31.792 --> 01:36.157
And then we have started a consideration of the teaching of this passage.

01:36.578 --> 01:47.310
I suggested you could divide it into four sections, exposition, teaching, the problem raised, and general application, especially at this present time.

01:47.630 --> 01:50.834
Now, we are at the moment looking at the teaching.

01:52.514 --> 02:14.215
And last Friday night we saw that the teaching here in the first instance is this, that our greatest danger always as long as we are in this world, even as Christian people, is our pride, our false conceit of our soul leading to pride.

02:15.436 --> 02:21.522
And we saw how the puzzle deals with it and teaches us how to deal with it and how to answer it.

02:23.426 --> 02:35.065
The second thing we saw in the teaching was that the apostle emphasizes the constant need of humility, the need indeed of watchfulness and of fear.

02:37.549 --> 02:41.796
He says, be not high-minded, but fear.

02:42.457 --> 02:44.380
Now he's addressing Christian people, remember.

02:45.341 --> 02:46.363
That is what he says to him.

02:47.184 --> 02:50.770
Be not high-minded, but fear.

02:52.482 --> 03:11.226
And he goes on repeating this warning to them to be careful and to watch and to take heed as we look at ourselves and consider ourselves in the economy of God.

03:13.028 --> 03:17.554
The fundamental theme you see is the Christian Church.

03:18.626 --> 03:24.652
and the respective positions and relations of the Jews and the Gentiles in their church.

03:25.273 --> 03:38.185
He's been telling them that the first branches, the natural branches were the Jews, but at this time they'd been broken off and the Gentiles had been grafted in.

03:38.686 --> 03:47.154
And because of that, this terrible danger had arisen for the Gentiles to lose their heads, to be proud of themselves, to burst us against the Jews,

03:47.266 --> 03:50.551
and to say they were taken out in order that we might be put in.

03:50.991 --> 03:55.778
In other words, the danger of falling into the very error into which the Jews themselves had fallen.

03:55.959 --> 03:58.783
Their trouble was, they said, we are the people of God.

04:00.525 --> 04:02.408
Nothing else mattered.

04:02.428 --> 04:10.680
They felt there was something peculiar and special about themselves, and in their foolish bursting of Jews, they were outside the kingdom of God.

04:10.860 --> 04:14.866
Now the Gentiles attempted to do exactly the same thing, and that is why

04:15.138 --> 04:16.760
This teaching is so important.

04:16.920 --> 04:19.143
It's a danger that always besets us.

04:19.644 --> 04:25.032
I put it like this last Friday, that we've always got to keep our eye on justification by works.

04:25.753 --> 04:37.228
Even though we believe in justification by faith intellectually, we find that constantly there's other enemy tries to be insinuating his way back again into our thinking.

04:37.429 --> 04:41.394
We've always got to be watchful and fearful of that very thing.

04:42.082 --> 04:49.431
We come now to the third strength, if you like, in the teaching which the Apostle gives us at this point.

04:49.451 --> 04:50.452
And I'll put it like this.

04:52.254 --> 05:08.914
He tells us that the best corrective against pride, and all that the countenance is pride, the best corrective against pride, or if you prefer it, our greatest need always is to know God.

05:10.434 --> 05:14.340
to know the character of God, to know the truth about God.

05:14.741 --> 05:19.167
Now this is the message of this great twenty-second verse.

05:19.187 --> 05:25.096
Behold therefore, this is the antidote to burst not against the branches.

05:25.497 --> 05:26.639
This is the way to do so.

05:27.099 --> 05:33.769
Behold therefore, the goodness and the severity of God.

05:35.572 --> 05:39.378
Now this is what I want to consider with you in particular this evening.

05:40.994 --> 05:42.316
What is this teaching?

05:42.336 --> 05:45.240
Well, putting it generally, we can put it like this.

05:47.484 --> 05:59.362
The whole of our thinking should always be controlled by our knowledge of God, by the truth concerning God.

06:00.724 --> 06:06.973
That's to be the controlling factor in our whole outlook, in all our thinking, in everything we do.

06:08.235 --> 06:10.098
It's all to be dominated.

06:10.242 --> 06:13.906
and controlled by thoughts of God.

06:16.848 --> 06:25.377
In other words, our greatest need is to know God as he has revealed himself to us in the scriptures.

06:25.397 --> 06:30.862
And if we have that knowledge, it will save us from most of our troubles.

06:32.424 --> 06:35.006
That's what he's laying down here as a proposition.

06:37.328 --> 06:39.090
Or I'll put that in its negative form.

06:40.578 --> 06:49.230
Our greatest latch as Christian people, always, is the lack of the knowledge of God.

06:50.271 --> 06:52.294
Now, that sounds almost incredible, doesn't it?

06:52.614 --> 06:55.478
But if the truth, it's the very thing the Apostle is saying here.

06:56.379 --> 07:04.209
These Gentiles were falling into this temptation to boast against the branches simply because they were ignorant of God.

07:05.471 --> 07:07.634
And this is the main cause

07:08.642 --> 07:10.764
of most of our troubles and trouble.

07:12.486 --> 07:30.447
So I put it positively by saying that the greater the extent of our knowledge of God, the freer we shall be in our thinking, in our practice, in every respect, from problems and troubles and failures and sin and final tragedy.

07:31.788 --> 07:36.754
Now, if this is always true, and it is, of course, the fundamental teaching of the whole of the Bible,

07:37.250 --> 07:41.695
I feel that it is especially true at this present time in which you and I are living.

07:42.797 --> 07:56.974
And never have we had a greater need of the exhortation with which this twenty-second verse opens, behold, therefore the goodness and the severity of God.

07:59.056 --> 07:59.737
Let's look at this.

08:00.939 --> 08:07.186
That's what makes this passage of, I say, such a crucial one, such an all-important one.

08:07.426 --> 08:20.005
the greater puzzle with his pastoral heart turned aside from the mere statement of prophetic truth, if you like, to apply it to these Gentiles, for we need it above everything else.

08:20.266 --> 08:21.407
Let me put it like this to you.

08:23.210 --> 08:36.210
Let me show you, first of all, some of the ways in which our failure to realize the truth about God, many fists itself in us,

08:37.346 --> 08:42.653
Now, the first thing it does is that it manifests itself even with respect to our doctrine.

08:44.836 --> 09:00.616
If we don't start with this knowledge of God and if the knowledge of God and the truth about God, isn't there overarching everything we do and are as Christian people, the first respect in which it's likely to show itself is in the realm of doctrine.

09:01.677 --> 09:04.601
However, doctrine is going to suffer.

09:04.621 --> 09:05.682
Now, this again

09:05.890 --> 09:11.156
may come as a surprise to some of you, you may say, well, I'm a Christian, and therefore my doctrine is all right.

09:11.196 --> 09:12.457
It doesn't follow at all.

09:12.818 --> 09:18.084
If that were true, you wouldn't have an epistle to the Romans, and you wouldn't have any other epistle.

09:18.104 --> 09:28.856
The idea that the moment you believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, you've got perfect doctrine, and your immune from error is, of course, of all the felices, the most dangerous of all.

09:28.876 --> 09:30.898
The new testament is proof positive,

09:31.618 --> 09:41.914
that because we start the Christian life as babes and as children, we are always liable as Paul puts it to the Ephesians to be carried about for every wind of doctrine.

09:42.354 --> 09:51.689
We are liable to go astray, and there is even a phrase which talks about making shipwreck of the faith, apart from this tremendous warming here.

09:52.710 --> 10:00.562
Goodness toward thee, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise thou also shall be cut off.

10:00.930 --> 10:05.736
How does it affect itself, manifest itself in the matter of doctrine?

10:05.756 --> 10:08.840
Well, I would start by putting it like this.

10:11.163 --> 10:17.631
The first way in which it serves itself is in a tendency to ignore God altogether.

10:19.133 --> 10:20.535
But you say surely that's impossible.

10:20.875 --> 10:22.898
That's impossible in a Christian, is it?

10:25.282 --> 10:31.752
Isn't it the case that so many Christian people today never seem to think not to speak of God the Father?

10:33.475 --> 10:37.341
They talk only about the Lord Jesus Christ and they pray to Him.

10:38.824 --> 10:43.271
You rarely hear some Christian people mentioning God the Father.

10:45.394 --> 10:52.786
Their thinking seems to be entirely concentrated on the Lord Jesus Christ through the exclusion of God the Father.

10:53.698 --> 10:55.762
It's an amazing thing, but it's true.

10:57.025 --> 11:01.554
That's one of the ways, then, in which it manifests itself, that he's rarely forgotten.

11:02.957 --> 11:05.322
If you ask them if they believe in God, of course, they'll say they do.

11:05.543 --> 11:09.912
But I'm saying that in their normal thinking, they never think about God at all.

11:11.575 --> 11:12.818
The doctrine of the Trinity.

11:13.570 --> 11:16.353
has been a stumbling block to Christian people from the beginning.

11:16.673 --> 11:19.557
All sorts of heresies have arisen with respect to this.

11:19.837 --> 11:22.260
I would have thought that this is the common one at the present time.

11:22.580 --> 11:31.430
I have sometimes described it as the kind of Jesus' olive tree, which excludes the Father altogether in its thinking.

11:31.450 --> 11:32.651
And it's the most terrible thing.

11:33.452 --> 11:34.653
Well, there's the best.

11:34.673 --> 11:38.597
Or secondly, it may manifest itself like this, and this again is so common.

11:39.899 --> 11:42.802
But if they do think of God and speak about Him,

11:43.522 --> 11:45.365
their view of God is a false one.

11:46.927 --> 11:51.414
It's not the true view of God, it's not the biblical view of God.

11:51.434 --> 11:54.318
Now, you are aware of how common that is at the present time.

11:54.378 --> 12:02.310
These people who tell us repeatedly that God is land, nothing else, only love.

12:03.451 --> 12:13.426
They really have constructed a God of their, that is, angelic, the very thing against which God through his servant, Moses, won the children of Israel.

12:13.634 --> 12:24.372
who'd had said, signal manifestations of God and his power and his glory, the thing that mercies has to warn them above everything else is the danger of falling into idolatry.

12:24.392 --> 12:25.854
And it is a constant danger.

12:27.617 --> 12:34.108
You don't take the God who was revealed himself in the scriptures, but you have your own philosophical ideas of us.

12:34.128 --> 12:36.712
You say, I can't believe in a God who does this or that.

12:37.594 --> 12:38.615
You know, that's idolatry.

12:38.656 --> 12:40.178
You've constructed your own God.

12:40.898 --> 12:43.702
You've got wrong ideas and views of God.

12:44.583 --> 12:45.524
This is most common.

12:45.604 --> 12:46.525
I think you'll all agree.

12:48.127 --> 12:59.822
And then going on to a third way in which our thinking is affected of necessity if we don't start with God and if God doesn't control the whole of the thinking is that we will have a false view of sin.

13:02.986 --> 13:05.830
And we will have a false view of man in sin.

13:07.051 --> 13:09.234
Now, what is your definition of sin?

13:11.202 --> 13:17.749
I think you'll find that very often we tend to think of sin, simply as something wrong which we do, and at all.

13:19.231 --> 13:24.076
Something which makes us unhappy afterwards and leads to remorse, and so on.

13:24.096 --> 13:34.648
Or sin as a man letting himself down, or failing to live up to his own moral code and ideas, and so on, or sin as a sort of a sickness and almost a disease.

13:35.289 --> 13:37.911
But it's thought of entirely in terms of men.

13:39.153 --> 13:40.274
Whereas, obviously,

13:40.706 --> 13:45.452
in the Bible, sin is always defined in terms of God.

13:47.375 --> 13:52.282
Sin is transgression of the law, sin is disobedience to God.

13:53.503 --> 13:58.650
But if you don't start with God, your view of sin, of necessity, is going to be a wrong view.

13:58.930 --> 14:07.983
And in turn, as I say, under this setting, our view of men in sin is also false and defective.

14:08.003 --> 14:10.546
Now, this is clear, speaking generally,

14:10.722 --> 14:12.605
of the Christian church at the present time.

14:13.566 --> 14:15.389
Views of sin are discounted in.

14:15.449 --> 14:16.892
They don't like the whole notion.

14:16.932 --> 14:23.662
They say they can explain it away psychologically, and the man in sin we are told must not be thought of as evil.

14:23.702 --> 14:25.926
It's a terrible thing we are told to do that.

14:25.946 --> 14:26.787
We must do that.

14:27.168 --> 14:28.710
Man just is a bit ignorant.

14:28.750 --> 14:33.378
He still doesn't know as much as he should know, and he's only got to be encouraged and so on.

14:33.578 --> 14:36.242
The whole view of man in sin is involved.

14:38.018 --> 14:50.410
The idea of men as a lost, condemned, hopeless sinner is not coming today, and it's simply due to the fact that they haven't started with God.

14:50.430 --> 14:53.973
In the same way, of course, it leads to a false view of the Atonement.

14:55.014 --> 14:56.316
All these things hang together.

14:56.356 --> 15:01.080
That's the extraordinary thing about biblical truths and biblical teaching and biblical doctrine.

15:01.641 --> 15:07.026
It's a complete hell, and if you are seriously wrong at one point, it will affect all the rest.

15:07.138 --> 15:13.505
And if you're wrong at this preliminary first point, fund a mental busterlet, well, you're going to be wrong right along the line.

15:13.765 --> 15:20.152
The result is that the ideas of the Atonement today are tragically removed from what you get in the Bible.

15:20.453 --> 15:23.456
They dislike this notion of sacrifice.

15:23.476 --> 15:24.557
Let me give you an instance.

15:24.597 --> 15:27.841
I have it in my mind that it only happened to me this very week.

15:29.623 --> 15:33.106
The popular idea today of the Atonement is this, as you know.

15:34.348 --> 15:36.370
How often has it been said by

15:36.706 --> 15:38.729
a certain type of popular preacher.

15:41.012 --> 15:47.642
That's what's happening on the cross is that the Lord Jesus Christ is saying, though you do this to me, I still love you.

15:48.703 --> 15:51.527
Though you're even putting me to death, I still love you.

15:51.547 --> 15:56.935
Although sometimes put it like this, that it's God, the Father, who's speaking, and what he's saying on the cross is this.

15:57.216 --> 16:01.722
Though you're murdering my only begotten son, I still love you.

16:01.742 --> 16:04.466
That's the popular view of the Atonement today.

16:04.610 --> 16:07.595
of the meaning of the death of our Lord upon the cross.

16:07.615 --> 16:11.181
Indeed, there is no eternal death, but they call it the doctrine of the eternal.

16:11.601 --> 16:17.951
And that once we realize this, it will break our hearts and we'll just thank God for his love.

16:19.113 --> 16:25.924
Now, I say I had an experience which brought this to me very possibly this week.

16:25.984 --> 16:32.114
I was preaching in a certain place and at the end of one of my services, a young curate came to me.

16:32.610 --> 16:34.673
and spoke to me, and showed me something.

16:35.174 --> 16:47.572
He is still continuing a certain amount of training, and he'd have to write an essay for his examine of him, his particular diocese, on this whole question of the death of Christ and the doctrine of the Atonement.

16:47.592 --> 16:52.219
And he does, so he was a good evangelical young man, but he showed me what his examiner had said.

16:52.920 --> 17:02.034
He had said this, that this idea that God had punished our sins in the person of his own son was not only wrong, not only immoral,

17:02.242 --> 17:04.045
He called it near-brastfully.

17:05.667 --> 17:07.590
Now, there's only one explanation of it.

17:08.371 --> 17:13.579
The trouble with that examiner is his conception of God.

17:14.941 --> 17:17.004
He doesn't believe in the God of the Bible.

17:17.966 --> 17:18.947
He's an idolater.

17:19.508 --> 17:23.214
He's worshipping a God who has been created by the philosopher.

17:24.596 --> 17:28.362
The philosopher's God is always a God of love and nothing else.

17:29.063 --> 17:31.346
And so the doctrine of the

17:31.490 --> 17:42.100
girls by the bone, and in the same way, with this wrong idea of God and the character of God, there's no need of regeneration.

17:44.623 --> 17:50.028
You just accept forgiveness and you go on eventually to heaven, and all is well.

17:50.509 --> 18:00.178
We don't realize that because God is what God is, no man can possibly enjoy heaven unless he's been born again and has a new nature within him.

18:01.474 --> 18:02.275
So I'll let go.

18:04.759 --> 18:12.269
And just to complete my list, you get in the same way, wrong teachings with respect to holiness and sanctification.

18:14.893 --> 18:21.042
You will find that such teaching, again, just concentrates on how I can be delivered from falling into this sin.

18:22.050 --> 18:24.473
How I can be given power to overcome this temptation.

18:24.713 --> 18:27.356
It's all men, all directed at men.

18:27.757 --> 18:32.363
It's all designed to help me to overcome and to be victorious and so on.

18:33.504 --> 18:38.230
Never put in the context of God and my relationship to Him.

18:38.250 --> 18:43.676
And so it is not the biblical teaching of holiness and of sanctification.

18:43.696 --> 18:51.506
There is nothing that is more vital than that we should start where the Bible starts with the doctrine of God.

18:52.738 --> 18:54.520
always in everything.

18:55.220 --> 18:59.184
God and the truth concerning him must be the controlling factor.

18:59.204 --> 19:04.049
Well, now there it is hurriedly, and you can fill it out for yourselves in detail with respect to doctrine.

19:04.289 --> 19:05.751
But come to the realm of practice.

19:07.552 --> 19:15.760
And here again we find that this failure always to start with God leads to certain inevitable consequences.

19:17.042 --> 19:19.404
Look at it, for instance, in the matter of evangelism.

19:20.565 --> 19:21.426
Evangelism.

19:22.146 --> 19:33.619
is the first great activity of the Christian Church, evangelism, preaching the gospel of salvation to men, calling them to repentance and a belief on the Lord Jesus Christ.

19:33.639 --> 19:35.661
How is evangelism to be conducted?

19:38.345 --> 19:50.098
Although I want to try to show you, is this, that if you don't start with verse 22 of the 11th chapter of the Epistle to the Romans, your evangelism will show it.

19:50.242 --> 19:51.704
And it'll show it in what?

19:51.724 --> 19:53.707
Well, in the kind of general breeziness.

19:55.190 --> 19:55.610
Follow me.

19:57.052 --> 19:57.954
Jokes and laughter.

20:00.157 --> 20:01.038
Right and breezy.

20:02.461 --> 20:03.222
Entertainment.

20:05.125 --> 20:06.266
That's what happens inevitably.

20:06.707 --> 20:09.031
Because you see, you've got the wrong idea.

20:09.091 --> 20:11.014
You're going to do something for people.

20:11.054 --> 20:14.859
You want to get them to do certain things, and you want to do certain things for them.

20:15.060 --> 20:16.562
You haven't started with God.

20:17.090 --> 20:21.895
And so the atmosphere may at times resemble a music called much more than a Christian service.

20:22.655 --> 20:26.999
But this is designed, you see, to influence people and to get them and so on.

20:27.540 --> 20:29.562
It affects evangelism of necessity.

20:29.822 --> 20:31.083
And it does do so.

20:31.103 --> 20:32.885
There's no question about this.

20:32.905 --> 20:36.849
It's all given to a failure to start with verse 22 of Romans 11.

20:37.810 --> 20:46.418
And then you see, it does in particular, it is what it tells because it's all emphasis upon man's needs.

20:47.330 --> 20:48.251
That's how it starts.

20:48.391 --> 20:49.232
What does man mean?

20:49.933 --> 20:54.078
Well, here's a man who's getting falling constantly to a particular cent, right?

20:54.138 --> 20:56.882
Now then, I'm going to tell him how to be delivered from that.

20:56.902 --> 20:57.663
That's how you start.

20:58.103 --> 21:06.434
You start with men, you start with his needs, need of a friend, need of happiness, need of joy, need of physical healing, and need of guidance, always starting with man.

21:06.934 --> 21:07.735
And man's needs.

21:07.976 --> 21:14.083
And then, of course, you're in competition with the other agencies, and your whole attitude in evangelism is wrong.

21:14.684 --> 21:16.306
The answer to all that is this.

21:17.826 --> 21:22.975
Man's only need, ultimately, is to be reconciled to God.

21:24.077 --> 21:26.180
Nothing else.

21:26.200 --> 21:28.143
I think I was putting it here last Sunday night.

21:28.564 --> 21:31.169
These things are so much needed at the present time.

21:31.229 --> 21:40.144
You see, if you start with men and men's needs, you will find there are a large number of people in this country today who are not interested in your evangelism.

21:41.085 --> 21:42.107
They say, but I never do that.

21:42.187 --> 21:43.890
I've never been guilty of that sin.

21:44.034 --> 21:47.760
highly moral, intellectual people living a good life and trying to help others.

21:48.180 --> 21:54.770
There they are sitting in their self-contained homes, and they don't see any need of coming to Christ.

21:56.272 --> 21:57.534
There's only one explanation.

21:59.457 --> 22:00.819
They know nothing about God.

22:03.283 --> 22:10.834
There is only one way to show that everybody needs Christ, and that is to hold them face to face with God.

22:11.842 --> 22:21.575
Then the whole world lies guilty before God, and there is none righteous, nor not one, all of sin, and comes short of the glory of God.

22:22.737 --> 22:30.788
You see, how it affects our necessity, our whole approach to the unbeliever, and the whole method in evangelism, and so you get wrong appeal.

22:31.989 --> 22:36.696
You actually get evangelists sometimes saying, come, God needs you.

22:37.857 --> 22:38.638
Have you heard that?

22:39.299 --> 22:39.980
It's quite common.

22:40.361 --> 22:41.362
God needs you.

22:42.658 --> 22:49.128
or it's put in the form of the benefits of salvation, how foolish you are, come if only you came.

22:49.168 --> 22:52.713
This is what you'll get, and so the things are put before them.

22:52.733 --> 22:55.557
And the result is that you get people coming forward to give testimonies.

22:56.218 --> 22:56.679
I've heard it.

22:57.039 --> 23:00.965
I used to hear it very frequently at one time, and it was thought to be so wonderful.

23:01.386 --> 23:04.651
I remember a man who used to get up, and he always gave this same bit of testimony.

23:05.151 --> 23:08.636
He said, I've accepted the Lord Jesus Christ.

23:08.697 --> 23:12.402
He said, 25 years ago, and I've never regretted it.

23:13.474 --> 23:14.996
I'm patronizing how nice of him.

23:16.318 --> 23:24.371
I've never regretted it, as if there was even a shadow of a possibility of ever regretting it.

23:24.391 --> 23:31.803
But you see, this is all because it doesn't start where evangelism and everything else should start.

23:32.183 --> 23:41.458
And of course, when you get to the point of pressure being brought to bear upon people to take an immediate decision, it's still further wrong.

23:42.626 --> 23:45.329
No, no, this isn't New Testament evangelism.

23:45.389 --> 23:49.793
You don't find things like that in the New Testament.

23:49.813 --> 23:59.722
The one thing that matters is our relationship to God and our need to be reconciled to Him.

24:00.843 --> 24:04.607
That's why I've always said true evangelism is not interested in particular sin.

24:05.668 --> 24:09.792
Doesn't matter what the sin is, everybody's a sinner.

24:09.812 --> 24:11.954
And we mustn't particularize about the sin.

24:12.930 --> 24:14.692
It puts the emphasis in the wrong place.

24:14.952 --> 24:16.253
It creates a false interest.

24:16.854 --> 24:17.494
No, no.

24:17.514 --> 24:26.083
What we've got to realize, according to the Bible, is this God and man, any man and the need of reconciliation.

24:27.284 --> 24:32.449
Well, there it is in the evangelism, but come on this practical point to something further.

24:33.810 --> 24:42.098
A thing that follows, as I've just been hinting is this, that you get a false emphasis placed upon experiences of necessity.

24:42.690 --> 24:51.063
See, if you start with man and think of salvation as something that does something for man, well then of course, a testament is helped, because here it is.

24:51.103 --> 24:52.685
I mean, get up and say, I was once like that.

24:52.745 --> 24:53.526
I'm no longer like that.

24:53.566 --> 24:54.588
This is how I am now.

24:54.608 --> 24:55.409
You can be the same.

24:55.629 --> 24:59.575
And he's only interested in being the same as you, or in having a particular experience.

25:00.076 --> 25:02.680
But you see, that isn't the object of the preaching of the gospel.

25:02.740 --> 25:05.003
It isn't the object of the whole message of the Bible.

25:05.204 --> 25:06.986
It is to bring us to a knowledge of God.

25:09.811 --> 25:12.114
The Apostle Peter puts it in a memorable phrase,

25:12.194 --> 25:18.482
He says that our Lord died in order to bring us to God, to this knowledge of God.

25:19.983 --> 25:21.165
Don't misunderstand me.

25:21.305 --> 25:24.789
Thank God for every experience, whatever form it takes.

25:25.290 --> 25:28.934
But you know, the primary business of the gospel is not to give us experiences.

25:30.176 --> 25:32.979
It is the potter's right with God.

25:35.462 --> 25:38.706
And then as I say, these false ideas of

25:38.946 --> 25:42.532
holiness tend to come in, and they come in in practice also.

25:44.054 --> 25:49.142
And we think of holiness in terms of deliverance from particular sins, but that's not its object.

25:49.482 --> 25:57.154
The object of holiness is to bring us into fellowship with God, that we may enjoy this fellowship, is to prepare us for Him.

25:57.174 --> 26:07.250
It must all be thought of always in terms of this fundamental relationship to God.

26:08.418 --> 26:11.543
Not some feeling you are going to get, or not some experience you may get.

26:11.803 --> 26:12.304
No, no, no.

26:13.566 --> 26:22.659
But I gave you this deep knowledge and to lead to a communion that goes on ever deeply so that eventually you shall have the beatific vision.

26:23.521 --> 26:28.007
Blessed are the pure in heart for they shall see God.

26:29.550 --> 26:32.434
That's the object of holiness.

26:32.866 --> 26:37.771
It includes deliverance from sins and so on, but you don't stop at that because that's negative.

26:37.951 --> 26:39.392
You're always looking back.

26:39.412 --> 26:41.714
You look forward, the vision of God.

26:42.115 --> 26:46.039
That's the motive for holiness and there is to be no other.

26:47.200 --> 26:59.331
And then in turn, you see, failure to start at the right place leads as the apostle is emphasizing here in particular to all sorts and forms of pride.

26:59.391 --> 27:02.354
Pride, this devastating thing.

27:03.074 --> 27:04.536
tried in our own activities.

27:04.676 --> 27:06.699
So, of course, in their clever and subtle, we are.

27:07.440 --> 27:11.246
We say, well, I'm not advertising, I'm saying, I'm reporting this for the glory of God.

27:11.566 --> 27:15.752
No, sir, I'm not doing it that you may know what a wonderful preacher I am or what a great worker I am.

27:15.892 --> 27:18.396
No, no, I'm doing it all to the glory of God.

27:19.717 --> 27:20.158
All right.

27:21.860 --> 27:23.683
We are not ignorant of His devices.

27:24.985 --> 27:31.474
So you get men bursting of their activities, bursting of their holiness even, bursting of their experiences.

27:31.906 --> 27:38.492
calling attention always to themselves in some shape or form and not to God.

27:39.273 --> 27:43.077
This is how it works out in practice.

27:43.097 --> 27:45.599
And let me sum it all up by putting it like this.

27:47.521 --> 28:01.234
What failure to realize is the truth of this twenty-second verse in the 11th chapter of the Epistle to the Romans always leads to his lack of godliness.

28:01.922 --> 28:04.246
a lack of the fear of the Lord.

28:05.407 --> 28:15.964
It leads to a lightness, a glibness, a superficiality, a self-contentment, and finally, this ugly burstfulness.

28:17.085 --> 28:23.115
My dear friends, am I not right when I say that this is the greatest trouble at the present time?

28:23.395 --> 28:27.762
We don't even use the word godliness as our fathers used to use it.

28:28.226 --> 28:32.351
How often do you hear about people talking about the fear of the Lord?

28:32.671 --> 28:35.235
But you see, those are the terms that are used in the Bible.

28:35.495 --> 28:49.111
Take, for instance, in that most lyrical book, the book of the Acts of the Apostles, I read this in chapter 9 and verse 31, then that the church is rest throughout all Judea and Galilean Samaria, and we're 85.

28:50.113 --> 28:57.842
And walking in the fear of the Lord and the comfort of the Holy Ghost were multiplied.

28:59.010 --> 29:05.060
Why is this so true of us today that there isn't much evidence of the fear of the Lord?

29:05.380 --> 29:09.387
We all must be bright and breezy, backsmacking and happy and wonderful and lost.

29:09.928 --> 29:12.933
My dear friends, it's not in the Bible, the fear of the Lord.

29:12.973 --> 29:18.321
You start with God, godliness, these terms have gone out.

29:19.503 --> 29:24.151
And I suggest to you that they've gone out because our thinking has gone wrong.

29:24.792 --> 29:26.034
We've forgotten this verse.

29:26.530 --> 29:29.774
We've forgotten the fundamental message of the whole of the Bible.

29:29.794 --> 29:35.041
We are so subjective and so interested in what I can get and what I've become and what I am and so on.

29:35.461 --> 29:49.839
The approach is so subjective and man-win, but it leads inevitably to these consequences, which are so evident amongst us, unless God has mercy upon us very well.

29:50.380 --> 29:52.082
Now, there is the manifestation.

29:54.242 --> 29:56.765
Are this failure to be whole?

29:59.849 --> 30:04.755
No, then let's consider the answer to all that, as given here by the apostle.

30:04.775 --> 30:07.539
And the way he puts it, as I say, is behold therefore.

30:08.620 --> 30:10.342
Don't forget this therefore.

30:10.362 --> 30:20.735
That therefore means my doctrine, what I'm going to put before you, is obviously the conclusion you must arrive at, if you can think clearly from what I've just been saying, behold therefore.

30:21.997 --> 30:22.898
The goodness,

30:23.106 --> 30:25.691
and the severity of God.

30:26.432 --> 30:35.769
The answer to all our troubles is to know the truths about God and to believe it and to be subjected and subjugated to it and by it.

30:38.333 --> 30:40.677
Well, what is this and how do we obtain it?

30:40.758 --> 30:45.206
Well, the answer is we obtain it alone through God's own revelation.

30:46.768 --> 30:47.730
You've got to start with that.

30:48.354 --> 30:58.469
You mustn't stop asking, now I cannot believe that God can… The moment you say that, you've left the Bible, you've left revelation, you're thinking yourself, you're making your own God, you're guilty of idolatry.

30:59.311 --> 31:04.639
And it's the only word to use about these scandalous books that are still being published.

31:04.659 --> 31:07.383
You are honest to gods and down to earth and all the rest of them.

31:07.723 --> 31:09.025
It's sure idolatry.

31:09.947 --> 31:14.834
It's what they think, not what God has revealed concerning Himself, that is idolatry.

31:17.794 --> 31:20.077
Very well, we start with this revelation.

31:21.259 --> 31:27.087
But, and this is the thing that the Apostle emphasizes here, and which we must emphasize.

31:27.107 --> 31:43.250
You must not only submit yourself utterly absolutely to the revelation which God has so graciously been pleased to give of himself and record it in the Bible, you must not only accept that utterly and become a little child, stop your own philosophic speculations, but

31:44.962 --> 31:49.046
You must take the revelation as it is.

31:50.547 --> 31:51.108
What do I mean?

31:51.849 --> 31:54.652
Well, I mean that you must believe the word and.

31:56.253 --> 31:56.653
That's all.

31:58.655 --> 32:02.900
Most of our troubles arise in this realm because we forget the word and.

32:05.722 --> 32:06.443
What do you mean, sir?

32:06.483 --> 32:08.125
Someone will let me tell you what I mean.

32:08.946 --> 32:13.490
Behold, therefore, the goodness of God is the modern cry.

32:14.882 --> 32:18.366
The Paul says, behold there for the goodness, am!

32:20.748 --> 32:24.792
And it's because the modern world and the modern church is leaving out this am!

32:25.533 --> 32:30.758
The things are as they are, and I see no hope of restoration until we've restored this am!

32:32.600 --> 32:36.724
I don't see any hope of revival until people have got hold of this ambed in this verse.

32:37.705 --> 32:38.606
Then there'll be ambo.

32:40.048 --> 32:42.130
We've got to take the revelation as it is.

32:42.978 --> 32:50.468
If you pick and choose with revelation, you might as well be a philosopher, because you still really are acting as a philosopher.

32:51.530 --> 32:54.374
The philosopher, as such, is not interested in the Bible at all.

32:54.574 --> 32:56.376
He starts with his own thoughts and works it out.

32:56.697 --> 33:00.983
You say, oh, no, no, no, I believe the Bible, but do you believe the Bible?

33:01.003 --> 33:05.509
If you believe the Bible, you believe it as it is, you believe it as a whole, and you bring in this end.

33:06.030 --> 33:09.454
You don't take one aspect only, you don't say, I believe in the goodness of God.

33:09.775 --> 33:12.018
No, no, you've got to believe also in the severity of God.

33:13.154 --> 33:14.415
Godness and severity.

33:16.097 --> 33:16.958
Doesn't this search us?

33:19.120 --> 33:21.443
How much do we know about the severity of God?

33:23.465 --> 33:26.929
How much time have we given to a consideration of the severity of God?

33:27.149 --> 33:28.050
What do the terms mean?

33:28.230 --> 33:30.753
Well, goodness means of course kindness and compassion.

33:31.153 --> 33:32.134
What does severity mean?

33:32.435 --> 33:38.301
It means, this isn't my idea, this is the authorities are all agreed about this, whether they're Christian or not.

33:38.721 --> 33:43.026
It means severe and exact justice.

33:43.682 --> 33:48.768
That's what severity means, severe and exact justice.

33:50.029 --> 33:56.057
It's exactly what the Apostle has already told us in the 18th verse of the first chapter of this great episode.

33:58.119 --> 34:10.994
For the wrath of God has already been revealed from him against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men that hold down the troops in unrighteousness.

34:12.642 --> 34:15.526
That's what severity means, this wrath of God.

34:15.546 --> 34:16.387
He repeats it here.

34:16.727 --> 34:17.328
It's everywhere.

34:17.529 --> 34:19.111
It's, of course, the message of the whole Bible.

34:21.033 --> 34:22.856
But this is the thing that men neglect.

34:22.876 --> 34:25.179
And there are last many men who say they believe the Bible.

34:25.599 --> 34:28.423
Indeed, it seems to me this is creeping even into evangelicalism.

34:30.225 --> 34:31.948
Only one side is represented.

34:32.008 --> 34:35.052
The goodness, the love of God, the mercy, the kindness and the compassion.

34:35.352 --> 34:42.642
And we are hearing less and less and less about the severity, the justice, the righteousness, the wrath of God upon us.

34:44.738 --> 34:46.520
That's where all our troubles come from.

34:46.540 --> 34:47.942
That's why the church is as she is.

34:49.484 --> 34:52.348
So I would put this point in the third instance in this way.

34:54.871 --> 35:00.918
That we've got to realize, says the apostle here, that God always acts as a hurl.

35:03.081 --> 35:06.305
May God forgive me for using such an expression.

35:06.846 --> 35:10.751
I'm bound to use it in order to bring out this point.

35:10.771 --> 35:13.554
God always acts if you prefer it, unanimous.

35:15.234 --> 35:17.376
When God acts, the whole of God acts.

35:18.117 --> 35:21.401
God doesn't act in pause.

35:21.421 --> 35:28.549
God acts always in the light of all his attributes and they are all in energy and in operation at exactly the same time.

35:30.231 --> 35:34.195
All the attributes of God are always displayed together.

35:35.596 --> 35:38.059
The goodness and the severity of God.

35:39.761 --> 35:42.884
And we must never isolate any one of the attributes of God.

35:43.025 --> 35:44.306
That's the modern heresy.

35:45.346 --> 35:50.451
that the love of God has been isolated from all the others.

35:50.471 --> 35:57.038
And it's a form of idolatry, it's a form of unbelief, it's a form of philosophy and speculation.

35:57.058 --> 36:06.588
We must not only not isolate any one of the attributes of God still less must we ever play one of the attributes against the others.

36:06.608 --> 36:10.092
That's equally bad.

36:10.112 --> 36:12.274
Often men have done that, they've played

36:12.770 --> 36:18.256
The righteousness of God against the mercy of God and the mercy of God against the righteousness of God.

36:18.276 --> 36:21.580
They've played the goodness of God against the severity and the severity.

36:22.060 --> 36:24.984
You mustn't play them against one another, not only not iserithim.

36:25.004 --> 36:26.646
Don't play them against one another.

36:27.026 --> 36:30.810
God is always and God is everything that he is.

36:31.831 --> 36:33.533
God is goodness, God is severity.

36:33.733 --> 36:35.335
God is love, God is early.

36:35.776 --> 36:36.517
God is light.

36:36.897 --> 36:41.362
All of these things are always true of God and they're always true at the same time.

36:43.458 --> 36:57.752
goodness and severity, justice and mercy, righteousness and peace, holiness and love and so on.

36:57.772 --> 37:02.657
And this is, of course, the very special point that the apostle is meeting here and is emphasizing.

37:04.139 --> 37:10.605
He said, you know, if you begin to extract certain things as it were out of the character of God, you shall be in trouble.

37:10.625 --> 37:11.666
You'll go astray.

37:11.842 --> 37:17.868
and it'll happen to you as he accepted to these Jews against whom you are now bursting, but you're traveling the same road.

37:18.068 --> 37:19.710
That's exactly the mistake they made.

37:19.910 --> 37:21.551
They said, ah, God was chosenless.

37:21.792 --> 37:23.513
And because God is chosenless, we're all right.

37:23.774 --> 37:26.236
They've forgotten the justice and the righteousness of God.

37:26.416 --> 37:31.661
They've forgotten what God had said to them through Moses, recorded there in the book of Deuteronomy.

37:32.001 --> 37:33.263
I'm leading you into this land.

37:33.523 --> 37:35.925
Don't rest on your horse and say, we're all right forever.

37:36.306 --> 37:40.850
If you don't keep on, then that's God.

37:43.234 --> 37:49.743
Very well then, to drive his argument right home, the apostle puts in the word, therefore.

37:51.306 --> 38:05.426
Behold, therefore, he says, is it possible that there is anybody who isn't clear about this, that God is all these things and always all these things together and at one at the same time.

38:09.250 --> 38:11.372
He says, but the thing is seen so plainly.

38:11.592 --> 38:13.014
How is it seen so plainly?

38:13.214 --> 38:15.516
Well, verse 21 gives us a part of the answer.

38:16.698 --> 38:16.958
Listen.

38:19.300 --> 38:36.818
If you think that God is only goodness, and if you think that because God in his goodness is ever chosen, the people, that therefore it doesn't matter what they do, they're always going to be saved and all right, that if you're a Christian, you can play fast and loose with God and defy him and do things you know to be wrong, listen.

38:38.274 --> 38:43.743
If God spared not the natural branches, take heedless, he also spared not thee.

38:44.063 --> 38:48.350
This is a great demonstration in history of the character of God.

38:49.612 --> 38:57.885
It is one of the most amazing manifestations of God's justice and righteousness and of compassion, the way in which he's handled the Jew.

38:58.966 --> 39:00.448
You see it in the old Testament.

39:01.771 --> 39:04.635
They thought that they were because his people, they could do what they liked.

39:04.655 --> 39:06.578
He shouldn't show them that they couldn't.

39:06.754 --> 39:08.456
He'd rise up enemies and attack them.

39:08.476 --> 39:09.618
God would actually do that.

39:09.979 --> 39:12.122
He caused them to be carried away into captivity.

39:12.542 --> 39:13.884
It was God who did all that.

39:14.725 --> 39:17.409
He punishes his own people, though they are his own people.

39:17.950 --> 39:24.459
And he puts it in very strong and striking language at times in order to enforce this particular lesson.

39:24.479 --> 39:27.424
Listen to what he says to them through the prophet Ezekiel, for instance.

39:27.764 --> 39:34.674
Writing, remember, in the captivity of Babylon in Ezekiel 14, let me read two verses to you.

39:35.426 --> 39:40.532
Thus 14, though these three men, Noah, Daniel and Job were in it.

39:40.892 --> 39:45.778
They should deliver but their own souls by their righteousness, saith the Lord God.

39:46.118 --> 39:47.480
He repeats it in verse 20.

39:47.820 --> 39:54.968
Though Noah, Daniel and Job were in it, as I live saith the Lord God, they shall deliver neither son nor daughter.

39:55.329 --> 39:59.053
They shall not deliver their own souls by their righteousness.

39:59.854 --> 40:03.538
The Jews were always falling back on Abraham, Isaac and Jacob.

40:03.682 --> 40:09.709
No, Daniel, Job and so on, as if that was going to… No, no, not with the righteous and the holy God.

40:09.729 --> 40:12.932
God cannot do that sort of thing.

40:12.953 --> 40:14.074
God cannot lie.

40:14.394 --> 40:16.356
God cannot contradict his own nature.

40:16.657 --> 40:22.984
And he's given this amazing demonstration of this in the history of the world, in his handling of his own people.

40:24.125 --> 40:26.187
Though there is own people, he punishes.

40:26.228 --> 40:31.954
And here at this point, he's actually, as it were, cast them off temporarily.

40:32.546 --> 40:40.798
plucked them off the tree, thrown them aside as branches that are useless and worthless.

40:40.818 --> 40:47.589
But there isn't the most striking illustration in history of this principle.

40:48.390 --> 40:50.633
There is something that rises even above this.

40:51.394 --> 40:53.838
There in the Old Testament is the most amazing thing of all.

40:54.359 --> 40:59.006
And in this dealing of God with the Jews as regards to the church, you get it as I say, repeated.

40:59.466 --> 41:01.970
But if you really want to see

41:02.050 --> 41:08.516
The goodness and the severity of God being manifested together, do you know where you find it?

41:09.337 --> 41:11.099
On the Cross and Calvary's Hill.

41:15.663 --> 41:19.247
And there, of course, the apostle has already been putting it before us.

41:19.267 --> 41:31.058
You remember the great statement in the third chapter, verses 25 and 26, whom God has set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood.

41:31.266 --> 41:31.967
Set it forth.

41:32.027 --> 41:39.479
It's God who put him there to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are passed through the forbearance of God.

41:39.499 --> 41:49.775
To declare, I say at this time, his righteousness, listen, that he might be just and the justifier of him that will live within Jesus.

41:50.215 --> 41:52.159
Goodness and severity.

41:52.399 --> 41:55.884
He's always got to be just even when he's forgiving.

41:58.148 --> 41:59.570
Justice and holiness.

42:01.954 --> 42:07.480
are always there, and they must always act together, and they always do act together.

42:08.942 --> 42:18.993
That is why there is only one doctrine of the attainment, not only in the Bible, but which is true to the biblical revelation concerning the character of God.

42:19.013 --> 42:24.339
God's love, let us never forget, is our Holy Love.

42:24.359 --> 42:30.706
I say to the glory of God that God cannot forgive anybody by just

42:30.818 --> 42:32.760
saying, I'm going to forgive, he cannot.

42:35.664 --> 42:38.267
There was only one way in which God could forgive.

42:39.569 --> 42:44.916
It was by putting our sins on his son and by punishing them in him.

42:45.977 --> 42:50.703
He poured out the vows of his wrath against sin on his own son.

42:51.084 --> 42:53.226
He had set in thought as a propitiation.

42:53.507 --> 42:54.148
God's done it.

42:54.428 --> 42:59.154
That's his severity, working with his goodness, the two together.

42:59.682 --> 43:00.865
It's a holy love.

43:00.885 --> 43:03.029
It is a righteous forgiveness.

43:04.031 --> 43:13.472
God must always be just, and he's never more just than when he justifies him who believes in Jesus.

43:14.534 --> 43:20.146
Oh, my dear friends, never try to separate the goodness and the severity of God.

43:20.770 --> 43:24.173
They're all there, and they're all there together at the same time.

43:24.534 --> 43:27.297
Any other view of the tournament is hopelessly defective.

43:27.737 --> 43:31.041
You cannot understand the sacrificial teaching of the Old Testament.

43:31.341 --> 43:37.147
You don't know what John the Baptist means when he says, Behold the Lamb of God that take it away in the same of the whole world.

43:37.447 --> 43:41.191
You don't know why Jesus set his face, steadfastly to go to Jerusalem.

43:41.451 --> 43:44.074
You don't know why he said, I have come for this hour.

43:44.274 --> 43:48.018
I'm not going to say save me from this hour, for this hour came I.

43:49.442 --> 43:58.474
You don't understand what he meant when he said, the Son of Man is not come to be ministered unto, but to minister and to give his life a ransom for many.

43:59.995 --> 44:02.359
You don't understand why he was ever baptized.

44:03.720 --> 44:07.085
You don't understand, indeed, anything in connection with him.

44:08.787 --> 44:17.618
Oh, he came into the world at all because of the goodness and severity of God.

44:18.626 --> 44:29.378
It is because sin must be punished that the incarnation and all that followed have to take place goodness and severity, not one without the other.

44:30.039 --> 44:30.860
Don't separate them.

44:31.261 --> 44:34.825
Don't even put your emphasis on the severity alone without the goodness.

44:35.145 --> 44:40.751
Otherwise you're putting yourself in hell, my friend, in your reaction against the glibness and the likeness of today.

44:41.092 --> 44:44.976
Beware lest you go to the opposite extreme and say that God is only severe.

44:45.237 --> 44:46.418
Don't forget his goodness.

44:46.498 --> 44:48.200
Don't forget his grace and blessings.

44:48.220 --> 44:50.643
They're all here together at the same time.

44:50.884 --> 44:54.268
Believe the revelation as it is.

44:56.090 --> 45:02.799
